      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take lol. i mean, i get the chaos part, but weren't there supposed to be strategic benefits? like, wouldn't removing a dictator who was a threat to regional stability actually count as a win in some frameworks? why do u think people call it a failure instead of saying it just had bad outcomes?",
